line_1: And proud Sedition trod on Loyalty,
line_2: He, that when late Rebellious Seeds grew high,
Nor can a Royal Heart unmindful be

line_1: That serve for Interest or for Loyalty;
line_2: They then the difference of Men might see,

line_1: The same true Courage, and true Loyalty,
line_2: Sir, still in you we the old Hero see

line_1: Fed on the Manna of his Loyalty:
line_2: But when his Coffers were exhausted dry,
And prompts the throb of agony.
